Package: AutoML4R
Type: Package
Title: Automated Machine Learning Feature Selection Workflow
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Xinyu", "Li", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "lixinyu1033472712@gmail.com")
  )
Author: Xinyu Li
Maintainer: Xinyu Li <lixinyu1033472712@gmail.com>
Description: Provides automated machine learning workflows for feature
    selection, consensus visualization, and protein-protein interaction (PPI)
    hub screening. The auto_ml_analysis() entry point accepts a feature matrix
    and group labels, writes model outputs, and saves feature-selection results.
    The auto_string_ppi_analysis() entry point accepts a gene set, downloads
    required STRING resources when needed, builds a STRING-derived PPI network,
    runs 11 cytoHubba-style topology algorithms, returns the downstream
    intersection hub genes, and can draw publication-style UpSet plots for
    user-selected PPI algorithms. The automl4r_beautiful_plots() function generates
    publication-oriented per-algorithm selected-gene plots, diagnostic figures,
    expression plots, and Nature-style consensus voting figures.
